&lt;h4 id=&#34;solution&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#solution&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Solution&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We might only update the word vectors that actually appear!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;either you need sparse matrix update operations to only update certain rows of full embedding matrices U and V,or you need to keep around a hash for word vectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actually ,in PyTorch, word vectors are actually represented as &lt;strong&gt;row&lt;/strong&gt; vectors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
