&lt;h2 id=&#34;more-details&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#more-details&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; More details&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;why-there-are-tow-vectors&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#why-there-are-tow-vectors&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Why there are tow vectors?&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;center vector and the outside vectors&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To make it much easier to optimization by average both at the end.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;two-model-variants&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#two-model-variants&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Two model variants:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skip-grams(SG)&lt;br /&gt;
Predict context (&amp;quot;outside&amp;quot;) words (position independent) given center word&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuous Bag of Words (CBOW)&lt;br /&gt;
Predict center word from (bag of) context words&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-skip-gram-model-with-negative-sample-hw2&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#the-skip-gram-model-with-negative-sample-hw2&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; The skip-gram model with negative sample (HW2)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The normalization term is computationally expensive&lt;/li&gt;
